English: A dog sitting opposite
Español: Un dormitorio con una cama; un niño sentado a los pies de la cama

English: Hmm...
They look at the jar surprised
Español: Un frasco con una rana dentro

English: Leaves It
Español: (El niño y perro) miran (fijamente la rana).

English: and begins to search here
Español: El niño y el perro se van

English: to search here
it looks carefully
Español: (y el perro) se sube a la cama

English: stands up and looks inside something
Español: La rana está dentro del frasco

English: The boy looks out the window
looking from inside the bottle
until
and the jar breaks
and gets blown into smithereens
when suddenly he sees the dog
and caresses it
The two begin to explore the place
Español: el perro se levanta con el niño

English: They see something that makes them stop
In front of them is a wood
there is a hive in one of the trees
with bees swarming
The boy sees the hive
The dog runs toward the tree
and moves towards the hive
It sniffs
Español: El perro mira dentro del frasco

English: and approaches leaping
to the place where there are bees
Español: El frasco se le mete en la cabeza

English: coming out of the hive
The dog is on all fours
and exits fleeing
Español: Levanta y mira en el interior de algo

English: chased by a swarm of bees
Español: coge una prenda de ropa (y la examina incrédulo)

English: The boy sees an owl in the distance.
Español: Los dos se asoman por la ventana

English: The owl glides towards the boy
Español: el niño mira por la ventana

English: and the boy runs away
Español: (y) el perro (está) en la ventana con el frasco en la cabeza

English: at a certain distance the dog also runs
Español: El niño está mirando (con detenimiento en todas direcciones)

English: pursued by the swarm
Español: El perro está sacudiéndose con el frasco en la cabeza

English: The boy is running "Ahh!"
The owl flies over him
The boy escapes
Español: cae de cabeza por la ventana

English: and the owl pursues him
Hmm...
on the way he comes across a rock.
The boy climbs on the rock
The owl flies away
to a perch on a tree branch
Español: cuando de repente ve al perro

English: The boy climbs on the rock
Looks from one side to another
and sees something down
Español: Los dos empiezan a recorrer el lugar

English: It is a deer
Español: Ven algo que los hace parar

English: which looks at him in the eyes
Español: Delante (de ellos se extendía) un bosque

English: with the deer gazing at him the boy is scared and leaps
Español: En uno de los árboles hay una colmena

English: falls on the head of the deer
The deer puzzled with the stowaway starts to move its head
and to gallop with the boy on its head
Español: El perro corre hacia el árbol

English: The boy dangles between the deer’s horns during the gallop
The deer gallops
and gallops with the boy bouncing about
They run to the bottom of a slope
Español: al lugar en el que están las abejas

English: where the deer stops suddenly.
The boy falls off the stag’s back into a river
Español: El perro se pone a cuatro patas

English: creating a surface wave in the water
The dog also falls into the water
Español: perseguido por un enjambre de abejas

English: The boy continues to look around
Español: El niño ve (a lo lejos) un búho.

English: He is in the middle of the river
Español: El búho planea hacia el niño

English: On  his left he sees a trunk
stares
Español: A cierta distancia el perro también corre

English: "Quiet" he shouts to the dog
The dog is behind him // both stare for a while.
The dog looks at him from below without moving
Español: El búho vuela encima de él

English: The boy from above: "Don't make noise"
"Let's go."
"to that tree trunk"
The dog begins to walk towards the trunk
Español: (En su camino se encuentran con) una roca.

English: the dog stealthily
Español: El niño se sube a la roca

English: approaches the boy
The trunk is near now
Español: hasta posarse en la rama de un árbol

English: The boy looks at the trunk
Español: El niño se sube a la roca

English: The dog also looks at the trunk
down below is the frog surprised to see them
The boy looks surprised at the frog which in turn looks at him.
Next to the frog
Español: que le mira a los ojos

English: is a row of frogs
Español: Al ser mirado (por el ciervo) el niño asusta (y da un salto)

English: and next to it their progeny in a row
Español: Cae sobre la cabeza del ciervo

English: The boy and dog are looking astonished at the frog.
Español: El ciervo (desconcertado con el polizón) empieza a mover la cabeza

English: with a wide smile
Español: y a galopar con el niño en la cabeza

English: The frogs are on top of the trunk in a row from largest to the smallest
Español: El niño va a trompicones entre las astas del ciervo durante el galope

English: The boy extends his hand
One frog climbs into his hand
Español: galopa con el niño encima dando botes

English: It hesitates but stays on his hand
Español: Van corriendo hasta el fondo de un talud

English: The boy starts to walk with the frog in his hand
The dog walks at their side
Español: El niño cae del lomo del ciervo a un río

English: The two of them walk
Español: creando una onda superficial en el agua

English: into the distance.
[Applause]
